      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content</head>
         <p>This addition to the 
         <famname>Steptoe Family</famname>Papers consists of a
         manuscript written by 
         <persname>Kevin Conley Ruffner</persname>entitled, "My
         Country's Bleeding Cause: 
         <persname>John Steptoe</persname>and the Civil War," based
         upon his research in the Steptoe Family Collection, with
         source notes. The article was prepared for publication in 
         <bibref>
               <title>The Virginia Magazine of History and
            Biography</title>
            </bibref>.</p>
         <p>Also present are computer printout transcripts of nine
         letters from John Steptoe to 
         <persname>Caroline Hampden Leftwich</persname>of 
         <geogname>Bedford County, Virginia</geogname>, 1861-1862,
         edited by Ruffner and located in the Steptoe Family Collection
         (# 6515) at the University of Virginia.</p>
      </scopecontent>
